==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Platter
<hw>Plat"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Plat</er>
to braid.]</ety> <def>One who plats or braids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Platter
<hw>Plat"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably fr. OF.
<ets>platel</ets>, F. <ets>plateau</ets>. See <er>Plateau</er>.]</ety>
<def>A large plate or shallow dish on which meat or other food is
brought to the table.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The attendants . . . speedly brought in several large, smoking
<qex>platters</qex>, filled with huge pieces of beef.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platter-faced</ent>⟦br⟧
